metadata.name: Alleles #371
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

attributes.name: Genetic Profile
attributes.value: Detailed analysis of the presented genetic information suggests subject may possess markers linked to excessive episodes of obsessive compulsive tendencies and psychological projection, yet also has the ability to show excellent communication and analytical skills. Maximum potential hereditary height (excluding nutritional and environmental factors) is estimated at 183-192cm. Projected natural lifespan estimated at 112-122 years.

metadata.name: Puzzles of the mind #189
metadata.description:
This is abstract art based on mathematical structure.
The puzzle of your mind seems broken and rearranged.

Mode has 2 variations.
 - Normal
 - Black
Color has 3 variations.
 - 常磐-tokiwa- (Green)
 - 真朱-shinshu- (Red)
 - 紺碧-konpeki- (Blue)
Color Level has 2 variations.
 - High
 - Low
Square Size has 3 variations.
 - Small
 - Middle
 - Large

Tokiwa is a Japanese word meaning always the same. It's green like the color of evergreen leaves.

Shinshu is a Japanese word that refers to a dull red color like vermilion. It means vermilion in its natural state with nothing mixed in.

Konpeki is a Japanese word that describes a deep blue, very close to azure. It's like a clear sky with summer sunshine.

Controls (in live view):
 - Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
 - Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
 - Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 4800 pixel (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #705
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

metadata.name: Притяжение #128
metadata.description:
Inspired by Kazimir Malevich works, “Притяжение” features the connection between shapes, their positions and colours.
Although, as the work tries to develop further into a non-objective world, some real sceneries can still be associated with it.

——————

Rendering takes around 20 seconds at 60 fps, might take longer on older devices.
Press [1…6] to change an image resolution up to 10k.
Press [S] after the image is rendered to save it.

Created using p5.js.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

——————

hrunz. — Aug. 2022.

metadata.name: Anachronous #202
metadata.description:
This project is about the exploration of chaotic structures created with lines and blurry silhouettes. They work together to make the shapes emerge without revealing them completely and create dark and light areas that compose a feeling of depth and weight to the scene.

Some pieces are chaotic, some more ordered. Some have strong compositions, some don't. By zooming in on the details we can let our mind wander and start seeing shapes.

Best experienced in full-screen.

Press S to take a screenshot
Press M to take a high resolution screenshot
Press H to take a higher resolution screenshot (may not work for some devices)

WARNING: Project is using webgl, it may not work on some older devices.

Original artwork by William Watkins · Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: Zephyr #54
metadata.description:
The name Zephyr traces back to Zephyrus, the Greek god of the west wind, and refers to any light breeze. The flowing particles get pushed around by a zephyr, creating interesting and organic patterns.

Live Mode Controls:

- Default is 2000x2000 pixel canvas. Press “1” for 1000x1000px canvas, “3” for 3000x3000px, “4” for 4000x4000px
- Press 'p' to save a png of the canvas.

Created using p5.js

Licensed under CC BY-NC 4.0

metadata.name: TI·ME 0 #21
metadata.description:
How and when Time started has always been one of the biggest questions of the humankind, that is yet to be answered.

There are things we may know, and there are things we may never know. Though, one thing that may be considered as certain is that, it did not start before it was started to be measured.

* * *

This generative artwork is a gift to my dear collectors of TI·ME series (TI·ME I, TI·ME II & TI·ME III).

Any collector who is holding 3 or more pieces of any of the three TI·ME collections mentioned above at the snapshot time of Aug 22, 18:00 UTC, will receive a piece from TI·ME 0 sent to their wallet. One piece per each 3 pieces held, i.e., if you have 9 pieces in total from any TI·ME collections combined, you will receive 3 pieces. Remaining pieces (if any), will be sent to randomly selected collectors who have less than 3 pieces.

Thank you very much for collecting and for your continuous support. Only with that, I can continue to do what I love.

Press S to save as PNG.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART

metadata.name: The river #6
RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #708
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.
